  "prompt": "Why is Maybach Exelero so expensive?",
  "response": "The **Maybach Exelero** is an ultra-luxurious, high-performance automobile, and its steep price tag (reportedly around **$8 million**) is attributed to several key factors:\n\n### 1. **Exclusivity**\n   - The Maybach Exelero is a **one-of-a-kind vehicle**, making it extremely rare. It was custom-built as a prototype and never mass-produced.\n   - Only one unit was ever made, which significantly drives up its value in the eyes of collectors and enthusiasts.\n\n### 2. **Custom Design and Engineering**\n   - The Exelero was designed as a high-speed test car for Fulda tires, meaning it was built to meet specific performance and durability requirements.\n   - Its design blends luxury and aerodynamics, with a sleek, futuristic body crafted by German designers.\n\n### 3. **Performance and Power**\n   - The Exelero is powered by a **twin-turbocharged V12 engine** producing **700 horsepower** and **752 lb-ft of torque**, enabling it to reach speeds of over **218 mph (350 km/h)**.\n   - This level of performance, combined with its luxury features, places it in the same league as supercars like Bugatti and Koenigsegg.\n\n### 4. **Luxury and Craftsmanship**\n   - As a Maybach, the Exelero is synonymous with **premium materials** and **handcrafted interior details**, such as leather, wood, and state-of-the-art technology.\n   - Every aspect of the car was designed to exude opulence, appealing to ultra-high-net-worth individuals.\n\n### 5. **Brand Prestige**\n   - Maybach is a luxury marque associated with exclusivity and sophistication, often compared to Rolls-Royce and Bentley.\n   - The Exelero embodies the brand's commitment to uncompromising quality and performance.\n\n### 6. **Cultural and Historical Significance**\n   - The Exelero has appeared in music videos, movies, and pop culture, further enhancing its desirability and mystique.\n   - It is often seen as a symbol of ultimate automotive achievement.\n\n### 7. **Collectible Value**\n   - With only one in existence, the Exelero is a **highly collectible asset**. Its rarity and unique history make it a prized possession for car collectors and investors.\n\nIn summary, the Maybach Exelero\u2019s price reflects its rarity, performance, luxury, and the prestige associated with the Maybach brand. It is more than just a car\u2014it\u2019s a statement of wealth, exclusivity, and engineering excellence.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
